<br>
Some thoughts, and maybe you higher level/more experienced enchanters have some tips too.<br>
<br>
Now that I have reached level 50, I am exploring some of the rougher areas of the game finally.  No, I am not Mr. Uber or Mr. Twinked.<br>
<br>
Having learned most of my knowledge from places like Sol B and Lower Guk, I am finding its different in the rougher dungeons.<br>
<br>
Example:  Most times in Guk, when a mob resists mezz, I simply stun it and remezz.  If that fails ... I take hits while the mezz recharges and re-attempt mezz.  <br>
<br>
but, in the higher dungeons, I find that dont work.  That style equates to a dead enchanter, fortunately I group with a god like cleric.<br>
<br>
I recently switched out my spell selection to basically be:<br>
<br>
Tash<br>
Dazzle<br>
Entrance<br>
Level 4 Color Stun<br>
Level 24 Color Stun<br>
<br>
The rest of the slots are set for whatever else is necessary based on situation.<br>
<br>
The lower level stuns offer me extremely fast casting, and allows me to, essentially, chain stun if one is resisted.  The same holds true with Entrance and Dazzle.  Should Dazzle fail, I have Entrance ready to go while Dazzle is recycling.  If stun works and both mezzes are recycling I usually will slip a Tash on the mob then restun for a shot at Dazzle.<br>
<br>
Just remember for those of you who havent been to the higher end dungeons, the froggies in Guk are orc pawns compared to some of these mobs ....<br>
<br>
Thoughts? Comments?  Suggestions?<br>
<br>
Uerien Deadweight<br>
50th Chanta Tank<br>
